caption.text:
Pac-Man Universe Bustier ———————————————————
The #MasterGrammer here with the new artistic flex.
First released as "Puck-Man," the name was later changed to Pac-Man. The original Japanese name was Puckman, which evolved from the Japanese word paku, meaning "chomp."
Sculpted PAC-MAN bustier created from an irregular geometric shape I developed from pure felted wire.
I used the shape originally as an exoskeleton hat mold.
I felt the direction would read more avant-garde if I repurposed it’s intent.
I have been obsessed with PAC-Universe franchise since a child.
Being inspired by the boards,
The fruit and of course the ghost all made for a stronger concentration to the overall body of work.
I’m back on my saucy shit 😝.

caption.text:
Pac-Man Universe Bustier ———————————————————
The #MasterGrammer here with the new artistic flex.
First released as "Puck-Man," the name was later changed to Pac-Man. The original Japanese name was Puckman, which evolved from the Japanese word paku, meaning "chomp."
Sculpted PAC-MAN bustier created from an irregular geometric shape I developed from pure felted wire.
I used the shape originally as an exoskeleton hat mold.
I felt the direction would read more avant-garde if I repurposed it’s intent.
I have been obsessed with PAC-Universe franchise since a child.
Being inspired by the boards,
The fruit and of course the ghost all made for a stronger concentration to the overall body of work.
I’m back on my saucy shit 😝.

caption.text:
Thought I'd finally delve into the Storybook series of the modern Sonic era.  Even as a huge Sonic fan, I was very apprehensive about these titles because they were more motion sensor focused (not a huge fan of that kind of gimmick). I tried Secret Rings at a Gamestop a million years ago and wasn't super impressed by the waggly/on-track gameplay style.  Since their release the internet came crashing down on these two, which also sullied my opinion of them.  However, I can't call myself a Sonic fan if I don't, at least, give them a try.  Just to see it for myself (it also didn't hurt that they were only $2.99 each at my local game store 😁😁🤫).

caption.text: Savathun created for Byf's History of Destiny video. We haven't seen what Savathun will look like in game yet so I wanted to take some elements from Hive witches and Oryx to create a visual that I thought could exist in that world.  I'm happy with the results even if it turns out to be far off of Bungie's design.

caption.text:
*SPOILER WARNING*
-
Alright so, I beat Astral Chain, about 3 days ago. And ooohhh my gawd lemme tell you. This game, is bombastic. I give it an 11/10. Worth every cent tbh. The cutscenes were cool, fighting didn't get stale, it is kinda like Bayonetta's combat style, but with way more options. The story was kinda obvious tbh, but everything else made up for it. Customization was pretty cool, it has lots of content and missions to complete. Selfie mode was cool asf. Voice acting was nice, and just ugh, it was so perfect to me. Watch the clips I uploaded by swiping right (if you don't mind spoilers) 😍 THE MUSIC DUDE. UGH I LOVED IT. I'VE LISTENED TO IT ON YOUTUBE SO MANY TIMES LMAO. But yeah, I highly recommend you check this game out. 💕
-

caption.text:
Pac-Man Universe Bustier ———————————————————
The #MasterGrammer here with the new artistic flex.
First released as "Puck-Man," the name was later changed to Pac-Man. The original Japanese name was Puckman, which evolved from the Japanese word paku, meaning "chomp."
Sculpted PAC-MAN bustier created from an irregular geometric shape I developed from pure felted wire.
I used the shape originally as an exoskeleton hat mold.
I felt the direction would read more avant-garde if I repurposed it’s intent.
I have been obsessed with PAC-Universe franchise since a child.
Being inspired by the boards,
The fruit and of course the ghost all made for a stronger concentration to the overall body of work.
I’m back on my saucy shit 😝.
